snippet.textDisplay:
Lots of love to Kazi Nazrul Islam from Pakistan. Nandita is on another level.
Bengali poetry is like a gentle spring breeze, bringing a breath of fresh air and a renewed sense of vitality. It feels like that first drop of rain after a scorching day, quenching our thirst and revitalizing our spirits. And in those moments of longing and separation, it becomes the passionate cry of a lover, piercing the night with raw emotion.
